      "summary": "The Bulgae, meaning \\\"fire dogs\\\" in Korean, are mythological canine creatures from Korean folklore that chase the sun and moon across the sky.",
      "full": "The Bulgae, meaning \\\"fire dogs\\\" in Korean, are mythological canine creatures from Korean folklore that chase the sun and moon across the sky. According to ancient Korean mythology, when these celestial fire dogs catch either celestial body, they attempt to devour it, causing solar and lunar eclipses. The Bulgae legend represents Korea's ancient astronomical understanding and cultural interpretation of eclipse phenomena, blending shamanic traditions with observational astronomy to explain these dramatic celestial events."
